{"id": "impl-broker-ai-code-strategy", "label": "Broker — schema-first ABI v0.4.0 + drift gate", "level": 4, "band": "impl", "layer": "impl", "feature": "broker", "bin": "bin2", "priority": 2, "maturity": 0.92, "distance": 0.0, "status": "ships", "summary": "[2026-05-28 update] canvas-protocol v0.4.0 (Capability.json now carries 5 motion.* caps per ADR-056/057) + matchPattern + conformance fixtures + fuzz/conformance/drift CI; ADR-009 boundary module lands the trust-level service contract. AI agents build to schema; drift-detect.yml blocks divergence.", "why": "[ride] The ABI + conformance fixtures + drift gate let AI agents maintain the broker safely (schema-first, executable invariants). v0.4.0 verified in packages/canvas-protocol/package.json + Capability.json. Failure-if-absent: unguarded AI edits silently break the wire contract. Leverage: drift gate + boundary contract are the durable guardrails letting the bus evolve without regression.", "claims": [{"stmt": "canvas-protocol v0.4.0 verified; Capability.json enum has motion.schedule/observe/patch/plugin.register/replay; src/boundary + tests/architecture/test_boundary_adr_baseline.rs present", "url": "governance/adr-057-ai-motion-intent-capability.md"}], "refs": ["cv-broker", "bin2"], "val": 7, "origin": "manual", "manual": true, "by": "opus"}
