{"id": "impl-boundary-trust-levels", "label": "Trust-level type system (ADR-009)", "level": 4, "band": "impl", "layer": "impl", "feature": "capability", "bin": "bin3", "priority": 2, "maturity": 0.7, "distance": 0.0, "status": "ships", "summary": "ADR-009 TRUST_EXTERNAL(0)/TRUST_INTERNAL_AUTHENTICATED(1)/TRUST_CONTROL_PLANE(2) + CrossBoundaryCall compile-time check: a caller may only invoke a callee whose required trust <= its own; EXTERNAL->CONTROL_PLANE forbidden; LegacyRetirementCandidate marker. Trust derived from validated OIDC claim, not a header.", "why": "[ride] Bin3 capability as a TYPE: compile-time trust-escalation denial is least-privilege the compiler enforces, not a runtime check that can be forgotten. Failure-if-absent: boundary crossings rely on reviewer vigilance. Leverage: the type system makes the canonical service boundary auditable by tools (CC6).", "claims": [{"stmt": "src/boundary/{api_gateway,gateway_contract,legacy,mod}.rs + tests/architecture/test_boundary_adr_baseline.rs verified present 2026-05-28", "url": "governance/adr-009-canonical-service-boundary.md"}], "refs": ["cv-capability", "bin3"], "val": 7, "origin": "manual", "manual": true, "by": "opus"}
{"id": "impl-motion-ai-capability", "label": "AI-as-bounded-emitter model (ADR-057)", "level": 4, "band": "impl", "layer": "impl", "feature": "capability", "bin": "bin3", "priority": 2, "maturity": 0.55, "distance": 0.0, "status": "ships", "summary": "ADR-057 three-layer defense for AI/agent emitters: (1) Zod schema validation -> (2) capability check (5 motion.* caps) -> (3) cost gate (element_count*duration_ms/1000, 10s window, cap 10k). Plugin register = Worker isolation + 5ms timeout + WASM SHA-256 + ABI range. 'An AI hallucination can't escalate from animation to plugin registration.'", "why": "[build] First as-built reference of AI-as-bounded-emitter: least-privilege + cost-metered so an agent's bug can't escalate. Verified in Capability.json v0.4.0 + ADR-057. Failure-if-absent: AI emitters gate only at API level (T6 lesson 7). Leverage: this is the reusable spine for cv-intent — generalize the schema->capability->cost gate beyond motion to all agent intent.", "claims": [{"stmt": "Capability.json motion.* enum + ADR-057 D-17 three-layer defense; spec/canvas-motion G01/G07/G08/G14", "url": "governance/adr-057-ai-motion-intent-capability.md"}], "refs": ["cv-capability", "cv-intent", "bin3"], "val": 7, "origin": "manual", "manual": true, "by": "opus"}
